What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The data consists of 183412 rides and 16 variables of 4646 bikes over the period of one month (from 1 Feb 2019 to 1 March 2019) from and to 329 stations. The data has no duplicates but has some missing values in the start station, end station, gender and birthdate variables.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested in figuring out what day(s) in the month with the most trips. What time of the day has the most trips. What is the age distribution of customers and subscribers? is there a difference? what is the distribution of the trip duration?

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I believe the duration of the trip, the start and end times of each trip, the birthdate and user type can be helpful in my investigation.

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

The distribution of the duration in seconds is highly right skewed. When applying a log transformation on it, it turns to a normal distribution that is slightly right skewed.

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

When investigating the distribution of birth year, I found some values at and before 1900 which is clearly incorrect. There are also some suspicious values from 1900 to 1948. No transformation are made on the birth year because the correct birth year is unknown and it might be expensive to remove these outliers.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

It was clear that there is a peak in the number of rides daily in the morning and evening except for the weekends, where the distribution of the number of rides was normally distributed. Also, there is a decrease in the duration with the increase of age.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶
